      <item>
        <title>Peasant [Suggestion]</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Geyde]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>V2w is really incorrectly labeling it.<br>
Visit to win is defining a role in social deduction by what it mechanically does (how many buttons can I push).</p>
<p>It’s a survivor that actually has to actively do something to win. It will be put in a very bad position if it decides to go mindless claim.<br>
Discentive would fix something because it would have to actively fakeclaim and avoid attention.<br>
Kingmaker scenario solved by making it suicide upon winning.<br>
It’s not boring because you have to play the game actively. Autopilot doesn’t work.</p>
<p>It fixes all of your problems mentioned earlier</p>
<p>Boring - It has to fakeclaim and avoid attention<br>
Uninteresting - This is purely subjective, but role that must find ways to dodge disruption effects and the lynch is a very simple role that doesn’t break the balance of the game in two due to swing.<br>
Kingmaker - Literally just make it suicide upon winning. It’s a very simple fix.</p>
          <p><a href="https://fol-archive.netlify.app/t/peasant-suggestion/76633/73">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
